other_tests.findings: Moderate-to-large amount of inflammatory stranding in the upper abdomen centered around the pancreas, likely secondary inflammation and thickening of the proximal duodenum. Absence of intravenous contrast limits evaluation of abdominal parenchymal organs and vasculature. Trace fluid around the liver tracking into the right anterior pararenal space and in both paracolic gutters. Multiple bilateral renal cystic lesions measured up to 8.7 cm in the left kidney. Urinary bladder is moderately distended with fluid and prostate is moderately enlarged. No signs of obstruction or abnormal intra-abdominal lymphadenopathy.
